    • Method Detail

      • getTotalDistance

        public double getTotalDistance()
        Description copied from class: Tour
        Return the total distance of this tour. The total distance includes the distance between the last and first point in this tour (i.e. the distance required to return to the starting position). If getWorld().getNbPoints() is less than or equal to one, then this method returns 0.
        Specified by:
        getTotalDistance in class Tour

      • getMSTRoot

        public Point getMSTRoot()
        Return the root of the MST used to construct the visit sequence. This method returns null if and only if getWorld().getPoints() is empty.

      • getMST

        public java.util.List<MinimalSpanningTreeTour.MSTEdge> getMST()
        Return the edges on the MST used to construct the visit sequence. The result of this method is never null.

      • getVisitSequence

        public java.util.List<Point> getVisitSequence()
        Description copied from class: Tour
        Return the list of points in the order they should be visited. The result of this method is never null. Each point in getWorld().getPoints() appears exactly once in result.
        Specified by:
        getVisitSequence in class Tour
